Watch Steve Reich's "Different Trains" performed live at Edge Hill station in Liverpool by the London Contemporary Orchestra.

The piece was written by Steve Reich about how, as a Jew, the trains he travelled on in the US during World War II could have been the trains to death camps if his family had lived in Europe at the time. It was composed for string quartet and tape, and first performed in 1988. The performance starts about five minutes into the video stream.

The performance was produced by Metal Liverpool, and live streamed by Boiler Room
